: This species is easily distinguished from the other Fijian species as the elytra have broad glabrous stripes and the flagellomeres (except the distal pair) bear numerous prominent spinules in the male (
<figureCitation box="[787,861,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6. 1–2" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,284,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[264,794,624,1332]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. 1–2. Xixuthrus ganglbaueri Lameere, female neotype: 1, habitus; 2, head, protho­ rax, and forelegs. 3–4. X. heros (Heer): 3, male; head and prothorax; 4, female; head, prothorax, and forelegs. 5–6. X. terribilis Thomson: 5, male holotype of terribilis; head and prothorax; 6, male holotype of heyrovskyi Tippmann [= terribilis]; head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030420/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Females (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1091,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6. 1–2" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,284,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[264,794,624,1332]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. 1–2. Xixuthrus ganglbaueri Lameere, female neotype: 1, habitus; 2, head, protho­ rax, and forelegs. 3–4. X. heros (Heer): 3, male; head and prothorax; 4, female; head, prothorax, and forelegs. 5–6. X. terribilis Thomson: 5, male holotype of terribilis; head and prothorax; 6, male holotype of heyrovskyi Tippmann [= terribilis]; head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030420/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) are further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lameere" authorityYear="1912" box="[427,571,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ganglbaueri">
<emphasis box="[427,571,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">ganglbaueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by numerous structural features, as mentioned above, including the longer forebasitarsi, apically swollen and spiculate scape, less produced medial pronotal ridges, and longer antennae. A few specimens have the frontal groove nearly as deep as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lameere" authorityYear="1912" box="[298,441,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ganglbaueri">
<emphasis box="[298,441,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">ganglbaueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so this feature seems of limited diagnostic value, though we have seen none with elytral pubescence of exactly the same color. Structurally, both sexes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heer" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1259,1323,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[1259,1323,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are nearly identical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1877" box="[529,631,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terribilis">
<emphasis box="[529,631,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">terribilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though the latter typically have a slightly more elongated vertex (
<figureCitation box="[355,495,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6. 1–2" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,284,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[264,794,624,1332]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. 1–2. Xixuthrus ganglbaueri Lameere, female neotype: 1, habitus; 2, head, protho­ rax, and forelegs. 3–4. X. heros (Heer): 3, male; head and prothorax; 4, female; head, prothorax, and forelegs. 5–6. X. terribilis Thomson: 5, male holotype of terribilis; head and prothorax; 6, male holotype of heyrovskyi Tippmann [= terribilis]; head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030420/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs. 5 &amp; 6</figureCitation>
) and lack elytral stripes. These latter two species share not only the male antennal spinules and long necks and mandibles, but also have the same pronotal and prosternal sculpture, and forebasitarsal proportions, in both sexes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1325,283,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,426,764,790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks</emphasis>
: We consider it likely that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heer" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[748,812,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[748,812,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1877" box="[869,971,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terribilis">
<emphasis box="[869,971,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">terribilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very close sister taxa, and they may or may not be allopatric; anecdotal reports indicate that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heer" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1079,1143,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[1079,1143,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may occur on Vanua Levu (not on Taveuni, contrary to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ryan, P." box="[787,931,844,870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref5320" refString="Ryan, P. (2000) Fiji's Natural Heritage. Exisle Publishing Ltd., Auckland, 288 pp." type="book" year="2000">Ryan, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1877" box="[1040,1143,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terribilis">
<emphasis box="[1040,1143,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">terribilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been found, and the 
<typeStatus box="[438,541,884,910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tippmann. Over" authorityYear="1945" box="[579,703,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heyrovskyi">
<emphasis box="[579,703,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">heyrovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is labeled as having come from 
<collectingCountry box="[1080,1124,884,910]" name="Fiji" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Viti</collectingCountry>
Levu, though no other specimens have ever been recorded from the island. As mentioned earlier, the 
<typeStatus pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heer" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[353,417,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[353,417,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is missing, but the identity of the species is not in doubt, so a 
<typeStatus box="[1145,1238,964,990]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">neotype</typeStatus>
cannot be designated (following ICZN Article 75.2). A male from 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1007,1004,1030]" name="Fiji" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1062,1004,1030]" name="Fiji" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Viti</collectingCountry>
Levu, Lami, collected in 2004 (not listed above), was selected as a genetic voucher for this species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="2 - 7" refId="ref5170" refString="Komiya, Z. (2000) Notes on Xixuthrus heros and its allied species with description of a new species (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae). Gekkan-Mushi, 354, 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="2000">Komiya (2000)</bibRefCitation>
has an excellent habitus photo of a male 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heer" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[826,890,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xixuthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[826,890,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
